## 5. Migrations — SQLite specifics

SQLite — limited `ALTER TABLE` (нет DROP COLUMN до 3.35, нет ALTER COLUMN TYPE).

### 5.1. Что SQLite supports

- `ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN` (since forever)
- `ALTER TABLE RENAME COLUMN` (since 3.25)
- `ALTER TABLE RENAME TO` (table rename)
- `ALTER TABLE DROP COLUMN` (since 3.35)

### 5.2. Что НЕ supports — workaround «recreate»

Для unsupported operations (ALTER COLUMN TYPE, ADD CHECK constraint к existing column, change PK):

```sql
BEGIN;

-- 1. Create new table with desired schema
CREATE TABLE users_new (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
  email TEXT NOT NULL,
  ...
) STRICT;

-- 2. Copy data
INSERT INTO users_new SELECT id, email, ... FROM users;

-- 3. Drop old, rename new
DROP TABLE users;
ALTER TABLE users_new RENAME TO users;

-- 4. Recreate indexes / triggers / FK references from other tables

COMMIT;
```

Документировать procedure в migration file. Frameworks (Alembic / Diesel / sqlx) делают это автоматически для unsupported ops.

### 5.3. Expand-contract применим же

Multi-step pattern из base.md § 7.2 работает для SQLite (ADD COLUMN nullable → dual-write → backfill → switch read → DROP COLUMN). DROP COLUMN supported с 3.35.

### 5.4. Frameworks для SQLite migrations

| Framework | Language | Comment |
|---|---|---|
| `sqlite-utils` | Python | CLI + library, popular for ad-hoc |
| `Alembic` | Python | Full ORM-aware framework |
| `goose` / `golang-migrate` | Go | Work с SQLite |
| `sqlx migrate` | Rust | Native |
| `Diesel` | Rust | Schema-first ORM |
| `Knex` / `Prisma` | Node.js | Both support SQLite |

