## 8. Encryption — SQLCipher

SQLCipher — drop-in replacement для SQLite с full-database AES-256 encryption. **Стандартное решение** для encrypted local databases.

### 8.1. Use cases

- Mobile app local storage с PII / health / financial data
- Desktop app password manager / secrets storage
- Sensitive local state на shared devices

### 8.2. Setup

```python
# Python example with pysqlcipher3
import sqlcipher3

conn = sqlcipher3.connect('encrypted.db')
conn.execute(f"PRAGMA key = '{password_or_kdf_output}'")
conn.execute("PRAGMA cipher_compatibility = 4")  # current SQLCipher version
```

### 8.3. Key management

См. base.md § 9.6 — keys никогда committed, не в БД с data. Для mobile:

- iOS: Keychain Services (hardware-backed на Secure Enclave devices)
- Android: Android Keystore (hardware-backed на TEE devices)
- Desktop: OS keyring (libsecret / Windows Credential Manager / macOS Keychain)

Derive cipher key через KDF (Argon2id / PBKDF2) из user passphrase + per-app salt.

### 8.4. Performance overhead

SQLCipher adds ~5-15% overhead на typical workloads. Negligible для most apps.

### 8.5. Alternative — application-level encryption

Если только некоторые fields требуют encryption (PII columns) — application-level encrypt (см. base.md § 9.4) с unencrypted SQLite. Tradeoff: less robust (DB structure visible) но flexible (selective encryption, searchability через deterministic encryption).

