## 9. Concurrency model

### 9.1. Single-writer constraint

SQLite — single writer at a time. Multiple processes / threads writing — serialized через file lock. **Not a bug, by design** — это price для no-server architecture.

Implications:
- **Single-process** apps (desktop / mobile / CLI) — no issue
- **Multi-threaded** apps — connection pool с threads serializing writes (most drivers handle automatically)
- **Multi-process** apps — possible но slow если много writes; consider external БД

### 9.2. Connection per thread

Standard pattern: connection pool, one connection per thread. Connections cheap (no network).

### 9.3. Long transactions — avoid

Long write transactions block other writes (no reads, since WAL allows concurrent reads). Keep transactions short.

### 9.4. Read-only connections

```python
conn = sqlite3.connect('file:mydb.db?mode=ro', uri=True)
```

Multiple read-only connections concurrent. Useful для read replicas pattern (one writer process + N reader processes / threads).

