## 10. Backup — SQLite specifics

### 10.1. File copy method

**Simplest:** copy `.db` file when no writes active:

```bash
cp app.db backups/app-$(date +%Y%m%d).db
```

**Не безопасно** во время active writes — может captured mid-transaction state.

### 10.2. SQLite backup API — safe

```python
# Online backup, even during writes
source = sqlite3.connect('app.db')
dest = sqlite3.connect('backups/app-snapshot.db')
source.backup(dest)
dest.close()
source.close()
```

`sqlite3` library backup API использует internal mechanism который handles concurrency correctly.

### 10.3. WAL-based incremental — Litestream

[Litestream](https://litestream.io) — replication для SQLite, streaming changes к remote (S3 / Azure Blob / etc):

- Continuous backup, low overhead
- Point-in-time recovery
- Multi-region replication

**Recommend для production SQLite** в server context (single-instance web app, edge deployments). Litestream — open source, MIT.

### 10.4. Backup verification

- Restore drill: open backup в read-only mode, `PRAGMA integrity_check;`
- Application-level: run smoke tests против restored copy
- Quarterly real drill: deploy restored copy as «production», verify functionality

### 10.5. RTO / RPO для embedded

| Storage location | Typical RTO | Typical RPO |
|---|---|---|
| Local file + manual copies | hours-days | days |
| Local + cloud sync (Dropbox/etc) | hours | hours |
| Litestream → S3 | minutes | seconds |
| User-driven (export feature) | n/a | user responsibility |

